  <sect2>
    <title>Installation</title>

    <para>
      Suppress installation of unnecessary files:
    </para>

<screen><userinput>sed "s/ install-info-am//" -i doc/Makefile.in</userinput></screen>

    <para>
      Prepare the package for compilation:
    </para>

<screen><userinput>./configure --prefix=/usr \
            --disable-static \
            --disable-nls \
            --enable-libgdbm-compat</userinput></screen>
    <para>
      Compile the package:
    </para>

<screen><userinput>make</userinput></screen>

    <para>
      Install the package:
    </para>

<screen role="root"><userinput>make -j1 install
rm -v /usr/lib/libgdbm.la
rm -v /usr/lib/libgdbm_compat.la</userinput></screen>

    <sect3>
      <title>Command Explanations</title>

      <para>
        <parameter>--enable-libgdbm-compat</parameter>: This switch enables the
        libgdbm compatibility library to be built, as some packages outside of
        LFS may require the older DBM routines it provides.
      </para>

    </sect3>

  </sect2>

